parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
often when the driver is braking or slowing down. The engine may rev loudly
and the vehicle may lurch forward or jump the curb.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The brakes may feel soft or spongy
or the vehicle may accelerate even when the brakes are applied. The driver may need to press the brake pedal multiple times or with excessive force to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control may not disengage when the brakes are applied
or the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly when the cruise control is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve body can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden acceleration, hesitation, or loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle seals can cause the differential to leak, leading to premature wear and potentially causing the vehicle to lose power or become difficult to control.
symptoms: The rear axle leaks fluid
the vehicle makes a whining or grinding noise
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate without warning, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the engine RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
